The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Dec. 29: Booming economy and vigilant tax administration have enabled the government to collect 42.64 per cent more money from direct taxes so far this fiscal. The Centre has mopped up Rs 1,46,051 crore in direct taxes till December 27 against Rs 1,02,394 crore during the corresponding period of the last financial year. This represented 69.32 per cent of the target of Rs 2,10,684 crore set for the current fiscal.

 New Delhi, Dec. 29: The countrys fiscal deficit in the April-November period touched 72.8 per cent of the budget target for the entire financial year. The Centres fiscal deficit grew to Rs 1,08,201 crore during April-November 2006. The budget estimate for this fiscal is Rs 1,48,686 crore.

 Mumbai, Dec. 29: The Nissan Copper scrip, which made its debut on the bourses today, surged more than 200 per cent over its issue price. The scrip closed at Rs 128.80 on the BSE. The company got listed at Rs 40 with a premium of 2.56 per cent over its issue price of Rs 39.

 New Delhi, Dec. 29: NTPC Ltd today signed a memorandum of agreement with the Ceylon Electricity Board and the Sri Lankan government to set up a 500-mw coal-based thermal power plant in the neighbouring country. The power plant would cost around $500 million and is expected to begin operations by 2011.

 Mumbai, Dec. 29: Bank of Baroda (BoB) has raised its prime lending rate by 0.50 per cent to 12 per cent from 11.5 per cent. The hike will come into effect from January 1.

 Mumbai, Dec. 29: Bangalore-based SK Birla group company Birla VXL has offloaded its entire stake of 2.62 per cent in Mysore Cement in an open market transaction. 

 New Delhi, Dec. 29: Honda Siel Cars India will hike the prices of its models between 1.5 per cent and 2 per cent by next week. A new version of the Accord is expected by the second week of January.




